<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Automated"><PMID Version="1">41370583</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>10</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>10</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Electronic-eCollection"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1984-0446</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>78</Volume><Issue>6</Issue><PubDate><Year>2025</Year></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Revista brasileira de enfermagem</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Rev Bras Enferm</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Gender Equality and Women's Empowerment in Nursing Education from the Perspective of the 2030 Agenda.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>e20240396</StartPage><MedlinePgn>e20240396</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1590/0034-7167-2024-0396</ELocationID><ELocationID EIdType="pii" ValidYN="Y">S0034-71672025000600157</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText Label="OBJECTIVES" NlmCategory="OBJECTIVE">to analyze the syllabuses of the mandatory subjects listed in the undergraduate nursing course pedagogical project regarding training for the 5th Sustainable Development Goal on gender equality and women's empowerment.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="METHODS" NlmCategory="METHODS">a qualitative, descriptive-analytical single case study that investigated the inclusion of the 5th goal targets in the nursing curriculum of a public university in Amazonas. The data were subjected to Bardin's content analysis. The emerging thematic axes were discussed in light of Bell Hooks and the Brazilian National Policy for Comprehensive Women's Healthcare.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="RESULTS" NlmCategory="RESULTS">three thematic axes stood out: addressing violence against women; discussion on sexual and reproductive rights; representation of women in leadership roles.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="FINAL CONSIDERATIONS" NlmCategory="CONCLUSIONS">analysis revealed gaps in the approach to gender equality in nursing training, requiring transversal integration of the 5th goal targets to train professionals capable of addressing social inequities in accordance with the 2030 Agenda.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Portela</LastName><ForeName>Ana Paula de Carvalho</ForeName><Initials>APC</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0002-2594-4708</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Universidade do Estado do Amazonas. Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Prata</LastName><ForeName>Maria do Livramento Coelho</ForeName><Initials>MDLC</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0002-8486-4484</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Universidade do Estado do Amazonas. Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Vasconcelos</LastName><ForeName>Milaine Nunes Gomes</ForeName><Initials>MNG</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0001-8815-0406</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Universidade do Estado do Amazonas. Manaus, Amazonas, Brazil.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Martini</LastName><ForeName>Jussara Gue</ForeName><Initials>JG</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0003-2629-293X</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Universidade Federal de Santa Catarina. Florian&#xf3;polis, Santa Catarina, Brazil.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Backes</LastName><ForeName>Marli Terezinha Stein</ForeName><Initials>MTS</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0003-3258-359X</Identifier><AffiliationInfo><Affiliation>Universidade Federal de Santa Catarina. Florian&#xf3;polis, Santa Catarina, Brazil.</Affiliation></AffiliationInfo></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Lima</LastName><ForeName>Margarete Maria de</ForeName><Initials>MM</Initials><Identifier Source="ORCID">0000-0003-2214-3